21.query: Counts all business days in a current month.

actions: #!/bin/bash # this script counts all business days in a current month. # get the current month and year. month=$(date +%m) year=$(date +%y) # get the first and last day of the month. first_day=$(date -d "1 ${month} ${year}" +%d) last_day=$(date -d "31 ${month} ${year}" +%d) # get the list of all days in the month. days=$(date -d "1 ${month} ${year}" +%d -d "31 ${month} ${year}" +%d | sort -u) # remove weekends and holidays from the list of days. days=$(echo $days | sed 's/\(0[1-7]\)/\1/g' | sed 's/\(1[0-2]\)/\1/g' | sed 's/\(1[3-5]\)/\1/g') # count the number of days in the list. count=$(echo $days | wc -l) # print the number of business days in the month. echo $count
